# Database Migrations

**ALWAYS** add new migrations as `.sql` files in `database/migrations/`. NEVER add inline migrations to `server.js` or any other JS file.

## Convention

```
database/migrations/
  807_challenge_matchups.sql
  808_race_division_config.sql
  809_team_color.sql        ← correct pattern
```

## File naming

`{next_number}_{short_description}.sql`

- Check the highest existing number in `database/migrations/` and increment by 1.
- Use lowercase snake_case for the description.

## File contents

```sql
-- Migration 809: short description of what this does
ALTER TABLE some_table
  ADD COLUMN new_col VARCHAR(255) NULL DEFAULT NULL
    COMMENT 'What this column stores';
```

## ❌ Never do this

```js
// server.js — DO NOT add migrations here
const [cols] = await pool.execute(`SHOW COLUMNS FROM ... LIKE '...'`);
if (!cols.length) { await pool.execute(`ALTER TABLE ...`); }
```
